An American Imam has been stranded at the Jomo Kenyatta International Airport (JKIA) for a week due to immigration issues; he was flying back to the US with his family. A senior security official at the airport said he was aware there is an American stranded because his country had denied him. &ldquo;I am aware of some American who is unable to travel back to his country for more than a week because of immigration issues. Americans have said they don&rsquo;t want him,&rdquo; the officer said.